    <thetext>When I view the PDFs for Rev 17 or 18 in Adobe Reader, most of the body text is rendered in Adobe Sans MM, which is what Reader substitutes when it can&apos;t locate the original font.

Original fonts appear to be:
    Arial
    Arial,Bold
    Arial,BoldItalic
    Arial,Italic
    Helvetica
    Helvetica,Bold
    Helvetica,Italic
    Times New Roman
    Times New Roman,Bold
    Times New Roman,Italic

Note that this problem doesn&apos;t occur with PDFs for versions up to and including Rev 16. Note also that the PDF&apos;s file size dropped by about 31% between Rev 16 and 17.

Looks like the same problem as in
https://mail.mozilla.org/pipermail/es5-discuss/2011-January/003899.html</thetext>
